OL,3,CGPs across England vote overwhelmingly
OL,4,Cto take collective action
OL,6,FGPs across England have voted
OL,7,Foverwhelmingly in favour of taking
OL,8,Fcollective action.
OL,10,FMore than 8,500 GPs took part in the
OL,11,Fballot and 98.3% voted in favour of
OL,12,Ftaking part in one or more examples of
OL,13,Fcollective action.
OL,15,FThe British Medical Association (BMA)
OL,16,Fsaid that it would now be asking
OL,17,Fpractices to choose from a list of ten
OL,18,Factions - such as limiting the number
OL,19,Fof patients a GP sees each day to 25
OL,20,Fand switching off NHS software which
OL,21,Ftries to cut prescribing costs.
