OL,3,CGPs across England vote overwhelmingly
OL,4,Cto take collective action
OL,6,FGPs launched a formal dispute over the
OL,7,Fissue in April, after a referendum
OL,8,Fcarried out by the union found 99% of
OL,9,F19,000 GPs rejected the contract.
OL,11,FThe last time GPs took collective
OL,12,Faction was in 1964 when family doctors
OL,13,Fcollectively handed in undated
OL,14,Fresignations to the Wilson government.
OL,16,FOn that occasion, it led to reform,
OL,17,Fincluding the Family Doctor Charter of
OL,18,F1965.
