OL,3,CGPs across England vote overwhelmingly
OL,4,Cto take collective action
OL,6,FDr Katie Bramall-Stainer, chair of
OL,7,FBMA's GP committee for England (GPCE),
OL,8,Fsaid: "We had a huge response to this
OL,9,Fballot, and the results are clear -
OL,10,FGPs are at the end of their tether.
OL,12,F"This is an act of desperation. For
OL,13,Ftoo long, we've been unable to provide
OL,14,Fthe care we want to.
OL,16,F"We are witnessing general practice
OL,17,Fbeing broken. The era of the family
OL,18,Fdoctor has been wiped out by recent
OL,19,Fconsecutive governments and our
OL,20,Fpatients are suffering as a result."
